Note:
==============================================================================
PROPERTY - Style Property Registry (CSS Properties Level 4)
==============================================================================

Registry of style properties with metadata: value type, inheritance flag,
animatable flag, and initial value.  Covers CSS Properties and Values
Level 4 (https://www.w3.org/TR/css-properties-values-api-1/) plus the
properties registered by CSS Cascade Level 5
(https://www.w3.org/TR/css-cascade-5/), CSS Box Model Level 3, CSS Color
Level 4, CSS Fonts Level 4, CSS Backgrounds and Borders Level 3, CSS
Display Level 3, CSS Position Level 3, CSS Flexbox Level 1, CSS Grid
Level 2, CSS Transitions Level 1, and CSS Animations Level 1.

Record layout:

  PropertySpec (40 bytes):
    off  0  name pointer        (NUL-terminated property name)
    off  8  value_type          PROP_TYPE_*
    off 16  inherited           0 or 1
    off 24  animatable          0 or 1
    off 32  initial_value ptr   (NUL-terminated default literal)

The registry itself is a List of PropertySpec records constructed by
property_registry_create at startup.  All ~300 entries are populated
explicitly to avoid dynamic-loading dependencies.

References:
  - CSS Cascade 5:       https://www.w3.org/TR/css-cascade-5/
  - CSS Values 4:        https://www.w3.org/TR/css-values-4/
  - CSS Box Model 3:     https://www.w3.org/TR/css-box-3/
  - CSS Color 4:         https://www.w3.org/TR/css-color-4/
  - CSS Fonts 4:         https://www.w3.org/TR/css-fonts-4/
  - CSS Backgrounds 3:   https://www.w3.org/TR/css-backgrounds-3/
  - CSS Flexbox 1:       https://www.w3.org/TR/css-flexbox-1/
  - CSS Grid 2:          https://www.w3.org/TR/css-grid-2/
  - CSS Display 3:       https://www.w3.org/TR/css-display-3/
  - CSS Position 3:      https://www.w3.org/TR/css-position-3/
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/markup/attribute.runa" as Attr

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VALUE TYPE TAGS
Note: ============================================================================

Constant PROP_TYPE_KEYWORD as Integer is 0
Constant PROP_TYPE_LENGTH as Integer is 1
Constant PROP_TYPE_PERCENTAGE as Integer is 2
Constant PROP_TYPE_LENGTH_PERCENTAGE as Integer is 3
Constant PROP_TYPE_NUMBER as Integer is 4
Constant PROP_TYPE_INTEGER as Integer is 5
Constant PROP_TYPE_COLOR as Integer is 6
Constant PROP_TYPE_URL as Integer is 7
Constant PROP_TYPE_STRING as Integer is 8
Constant PROP_TYPE_IDENT_LIST as Integer is 9
Constant PROP_TYPE_TIME as Integer is 10
Constant PROP_TYPE_FREQUENCY as Integer is 11
Constant PROP_TYPE_ANGLE as Integer is 12
Constant PROP_TYPE_TRANSFORM as Integer is 13
Constant PROP_TYPE_FONT_FAMILY as Integer is 14
Constant PROP_TYPE_FONT_WEIGHT as Integer is 15
Constant PROP_TYPE_DISPLAY as Integer is 16
Constant PROP_TYPE_POSITION as Integer is 17
Constant PROP_TYPE_BOX_SIZING as Integer is 18
Constant PROP_TYPE_OVERFLOW as Integer is 19
Constant PROP_TYPE_VISIBILITY as Integer is 20
Constant PROP_TYPE_FLEX as Integer is 21
Constant PROP_TYPE_GRID_TEMPLATE as Integer is 22
Constant PROP_TYPE_ANIMATION as Integer is 23
Constant PROP_TYPE_TRANSITION as Integer is 24
Constant PROP_TYPE_SHORTHAND as Integer is 25

Constant PROP_SPEC_SIZE as Integer is 40
Constant PROP_OFF_NAME as Integer is 0
Constant PROP_OFF_VALUE_TYPE as Integer is 8
Constant PROP_OFF_INHERITED as Integer is 16
Constant PROP_OFF_ANIMATABLE as Integer is 24
Constant PROP_OFF_INITIAL as Integer is 32

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PROPERTY SPEC CONSTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Build a single PropertySpec record.  Used internally by the registry
builder; not intended for application code, which should use
property_lookup against a built registry.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Layout.allocate 40 bytes; write all five fields.  Returns 0 on OOM.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Strings borrowed; lifetime tied to the registry's lifetime.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "property_spec_create" takes name as Integer, value_type as Integer, inherited as Integer, animatable as Integer, initial_value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let record be proc allocate from Layout with PROP_SPEC_SIZE
    If record is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, PROP_OFF_NAME, name
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, PROP_OFF_VALUE_TYPE, value_type
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, PROP_OFF_INHERITED, inherited
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, PROP_OFF_ANIMATABLE, animatable
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, PROP_OFF_INITIAL, initial_value
    Return record
End Process

Process called "property_spec_get_name" takes spec as Integer returns Integer:
    If spec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with spec, PROP_OFF_NAME
End Process

Process called "property_spec_get_value_type" takes spec as Integer returns Integer:
    If spec is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with spec, PROP_OFF_VALUE_TYPE
End Process

Process called "property_spec_is_inherited" takes spec as Integer returns Integer:
    If spec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with spec, PROP_OFF_INHERITED
End Process

Process called "property_spec_is_animatable" takes spec as Integer returns Integer:
    If spec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with spec, PROP_OFF_ANIMATABLE
End Process

Process called "property_spec_initial_value" takes spec as Integer returns Integer:
    If spec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with spec, PROP_OFF_INITIAL
End Process

Process called "property_spec_destroy" takes spec as Integer returns Integer:
    If spec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with spec
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: REGISTRY BUILDER
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Append a spec built from inline arguments to the registry list.  Helper
to keep the registry-construction code legible.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
property_spec_create + list_push.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
Amortized O(1) per entry.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns -1 on OOM.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "registry_add" takes registry as Integer, name as Integer, value_type as Integer, inherited as Integer, animatable as Integer, initial as Integer returns Integer:
    Let spec be proc property_spec_create with name, value_type, inherited, animatable, initial
    If spec is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If
    Return proc list_push from List with registry, spec
End Process

@Reasoning
Build the full property registry covering ~300 properties.  Grouped by
spec section in declaration order.  Each entry encodes
(name, value-type, inherited, animatable, initial-value).  Initial
values are CSS-spec defaults.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Linear sequence of registry_add calls.  Returns the populated List.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(entry-count) startup cost.  Lookup is O(n) via the linear-scan in
property_lookup; for hotspot use, callers should build a hash index
once and reuse it.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
All literal strings are read-only; the registry owns the PropertySpec
records and must be destroyed with property_registry_destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "property_registry_create" returns Integer:
    Let registry be proc list_create from List
    If registry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: --- CSS Box Model 3 ---
